<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-146439" number="52958" version="2729">
			<HEADING>Chapter 37: Petitioning the Department to Commence Rulemaking</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19200" name="T24C037"/>Chapter 37: Petitioning the Department to Commence Rulemaking</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-146692" number="52959" version="2784">
								<HEADING>§ 37-01 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19202" name="T24C037_37-01"/>§ 37-01 Definitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146714" number="52960" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Department</CHARFORMAT> means the New York City Department of Health and Mental Hygiene. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146713" number="52961" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Petition</CHARFORMAT> means a request or application by a member of the public for the Department to create, amend or repeal a rule promulgated by the Department. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146712" number="52962" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Petitioner</CHARFORMAT> means the person who submits a petition. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146711" number="52963" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Rule</CHARFORMAT> shall have the meaning set forth in Section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1041" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1041</LINK>(5) of the New York City Charter (“Charter”) and, for the purposes of this Chapter, means only those provisions of law contained in, or to be contained in, <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="Title 24" destination-id="0-0-0-15486">Title 24</LINK> of the Rules of the City of New York with numerical Chapter headings and also known as Commissioner of Health Regulations (“Commissioner Regulations”). For the purposes of this Chapter, rule does not include any provision of the New York City Health Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146710" number="52964" version="2729">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/1/2024, eff. 7/31/2024) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-146715" number="52965" version="2784">
								<HEADING>§ 37-03 Scope.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19204" name="T24C037_37-03"/>§ 37-03 Scope.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146709" number="52966" version="2729">
									<PARA>This Chapter governs the procedures by which the public may petition the Department to commence rulemaking of Commissioner Regulations pursuant to Section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1043" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1043</LINK>(g) of the Charter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146708" number="52967" version="2729">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/1/2024, eff. 7/31/2024) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-146716" number="52968" version="2784">
								<HEADING>§ 37-05 Procedures for Submitting Petitions; Responses to Petitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-19206" name="T24C037_37-05"/>§ 37-05 Procedures for Submitting Petitions; Responses to Petitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146707" number="52969" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any person may petition the Department to consider the adoption, amendment or repeal of a rule. The petition must be in writing and must contain the following information: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146706" number="52970" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The rule to be considered, including proposed language for adoption; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146705" number="52971" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A statement as to the purpose of the rule, amendment or repeal and the Department’s authority to promulgate the rule; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146704" number="52972" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(3)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Petitioner’s argument(s) in support of adoption of the rule, amendment or repeal. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146703" number="52973" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(4)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The period of time the rule should be in effect, if applicable; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146702" number="52974" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(5)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whether the person submitting the petition represents another individual or an organization; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146701" number="52975" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(6)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The name, address and telephone number of the petitioner or his or her authorized representative; <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146700" number="52976" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(7)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The signature of petitioner or their representative. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146699" number="52977" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Illegible petitions will not be accepted. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146698" number="52978" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>All petitions must be delivered to the office of the Secretary to the Department by mail, courier, facsimile, electronic mail or online. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146697" number="52979" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The petitioner must promptly communicate any changes in the information required by this section in writing to the office of the Secretary to the Department. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146696" number="52980" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Upon receipt of a petition submitted in the proper form, the Secretary to the Department will stamp the petition with the date it was received and assign the petition a number and a date-stamped receipt with the petition number shall be sent to the petitioner. The Secretary will forward the petition to the Commissioner and appropriate staff of the Department for their review. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146695" number="52981" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(f)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Within sixty (60) days from the date the petition is properly received by the Secretary to the Department, the Commissioner will either deny such petition in a written statement to the petitioner containing the reasons for denial, or state in writing to the petitioner the intention to grant the petition and to initiate rulemaking on the subject matter by a specified date. In all cases where the Commissioner has granted a petition to initiate rulemaking, the Department is not bound by any specific language proposed by the petitioner. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146694" number="52982" version="2729">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(g)<TAB tab-count="1"/>The Commissioner’s decision to grant or deny a petition will be a final decision which is not subject to judicial review pursuant to Section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1043" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1043</LINK>(g) of the Charter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-146691" number="52983" version="2729">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 7/1/2024, eff. 7/31/2024) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-099]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
					</LEVEL>
				</LEVEL>
			</LEVEL>
		</LEVEL>
	</LEVEL>
</DOCUMENT>